{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:39:46.321967+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: e0f90ac88e1236616df18600c7f7a5f80ac113c6)", "id": "lc_6ab437c0-7fa1-48c3-a54c-cd2b69069320"}, {"type": "text", "text": "from datetime import datetime, timedelta\nfrom typing import Any, Dict\n\nfrom fastapi.security import OAuth2PasswordBearer\nfrom jose import jwt\n\nfrom app.services import BaseService\nfrom app.settings import settings\n\n# for authentication that works seamlessly with OpenAPI\nreuseable_oauth = OAuth2PasswordBearer(\n    tokenUrl=\"/api/v1/user/login\",\n    scheme_name=\"JWT\"\n)\n\n\ndef hash_password(password: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Creates a hash of the password\"\"\"\n    hashed_password = settings.PASSWORD_HASHER.hash(password)\n    return hashed_password\n\n\ndef verify_password(plain_password: str, hashed_password: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Checks if a password corresponds to a hash\"\"\"\n    password_is_verified = settings.PASSWORD_HASHER.verify(\n        plain_password, hashed_password\n    )\n\n    return bool(password_is_verified)\n\n\ndef create_auth_token(payload: Dict[str, Any], expiry: int) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    This handles the encoding of user information into a token\n    that can be used. It is generic so as to accomodate access and\n    refresh token.\n    \"\"\"\n    expiry_delta = datetime.now() + timedelta(seconds=expiry)\n    data_to_encode = {\"expiry\": str(expiry_delta), \"data\": payload}\n    encoded_data: str = jwt.encode(\n        data_to_encode, settings.SECRET_KEY, settings.JWT_ALGORITHM\n    )\n\n    return encoded_data\n\n\nclass UserService(BaseService):\n    \"\"\"\n    This class helps perform bulk of activities required by the corresponding API\n    \"\"\"\n    def a_method(self):\n        \"\"\"\n        Here, the use of `self.save` is demonstrated.\n        Ensure to take out this method.\n        \"\"\"\n        model_instance = ...\n        self.save(model_instance)", "id": "lc_5c940ec0-a87d-43a1-8639-1d153a3bb2ce"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "9fe7e0fe-18af-459f-a648-e70397629246", "tool_call_id": "call_9232eb938b08447b9da67d75", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:40:04.386233+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "## How Application Settings Are Derived from Environment Variables\n\nThis template uses a **centralized `Settings` class** in `app/settings.py` that reads environment variables via `os.environ.get()` and composes derived configuration values. Here's the complete picture:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Environment Variable Source\n\nThe `.example.env` file defines the expected environment variables:\n\n| Variable | Example Value |\n|---|---|\n| `ALLOWED_HOST` | `0.0.0.0` |\n| `SECRET_KEY` | `meandyouaretogether` |\n| `DEBUG` | `True` |\n| `PORT` | `11000` |\n| `POSTGRES_USER` | `sasori` |\n| `POSTGRES_PASSWORD` | `sasori` |\n| `POSTGRES_DB` | `akatsuki` |\n| `POSTGRES_TEST_DB` | `hebi` |\n| `POSTGRES_PORT` | `5432` |\n| `POSTGRES_HOST` | `postgres` |\n| `REDIS_HOST` | `redis` |\n| `REDIS_PORT` | `6379` |\n\n---\n\n### 2. The `Settings` Class (`app/settings.py`)\n\nThe `Settings` class acts as a **flat mirror of the environment**, mapping raw env vars to descriptive attribute names. A singleton instance is created at module level (`settings = Settings()`) and imported wherever needed.\n\n#### Basic Server Settings\n| Setting Attribute | Env Variable | Type | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `ALLOWED_HOST` | `ALLOWED_HOST` | `str` | Host to bind the server to |\n| `SECRET_KEY` | `SECRET_KEY` | `str` | Used for JWT signing |\n| `DEBUG` | `DEBUG` | `bool` | Cast via `bool(environ.get(...))` |\n| `ALLOWED_PORT` | `PORT` | `int` | Cast via `int(environ.get(...))` |\n\n#### Database URLs (Composed from Individual Env Vars)\nThe template reads **five separate PostgreSQL env vars** and composes full connection URLs:\n\n```\nDB_USER       ← POSTGRES_USER\nDB_PASSWORD   ← POSTGRES_PASSWORD\nDB_DB         ← POSTGRES_DB\nDB_PORT       ← POSTGRES_PORT\nDB_HOST       ← POSTGRES_HOST\n```\n\nThese are then interpolated into SQLAlchemy-compatible URLs:\n\n```python\nDB_URL = f\"postgresql+psycopg2://{DB_USER}:{DB_PASSWORD}@{DB_HOST}:{DB_PORT}/{DB_DB}\"\nTEST_DB_URL = f\"postgresql+psycopg2://{DB_USER}:{DB_PASSWORD}@{DB_HOST}:{DB_PORT}/{TEST_DB}\"\n```\n\nSo with the example values, `DB_URL` resolves to:\n`postgresql+psycopg2://sasori:sasori@postgres:5432/akatsuki`\n\n**Key point:** There is no single `DATABASE_URL` env var. The URL is *derived* at import time from the component variables. If any component is missing, the URL will contain `None`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Database Usage (`app/db.py`)\n\nThe composed `DB_URL` is consumed by two database clients:\n\n1. **`databases.Database`** (async) — used by the FastAPI startup/shutdown lifecycle in `main.py` for async query execution.\n2. **`sqlalchemy.create_engine`** (sync) — used with a connection pool (`pool_size=3, max_overflow=0`), a `sessionmaker` for dependency injection (`get_db()`), and for auto-creating the database and tables if they don't exist.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Token / JWT Settings\n\nToken configuration is **entirely hardcoded** in the `Settings` class (not from env vars):\n\n| Setting | Value | Meaning |\n|---|---|---|\n| `ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRY_TIME` | `60 * 30` (1800s = 30 min) | Access token lifetime |\n| `REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRY_TIME` | `60 * 24 * 365` (31,536,000s ≈ 1 year) | Refresh token lifetime |\n| `JWT_ALGORITHM` | `\"HS256\"` | HMAC-SHA256 signing |\n| `PASSWORD_HASHER` | `CryptContext(schemes=[\"bcrypt\"])` | Password hashing via `passlib` |\n\nThe `SECRET_KEY` (from env) is the signing secret used by `jose.jwt.encode()` in `auth/services.py` when creating auth tokens.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Redis Configuration\n\nRedis settings use `environ.get()` **with fallback defaults**:\n\n| Setting | Env Variable | Default |\n|---|---|---|\n| `REDIS_HOST` | `REDIS_HOST` | `\"localhost\"` |\n| `REDIS_PORT` | `REDIS_PORT` | `\"6379\"` |\n\nThis means Redis will work even without env vars (connecting to `localhost:6379`), unlike the database settings which have no defaults and would break if env vars are missing.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Additional Hardcoded Settings\n\n| Setting | Value | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `APP_TITLE` | `\"App name\"` | FastAPI app title |\n| `PAGE_SIZE` | `50` | Default pagination size |\n\n---\n\n### Summary Flow\n\n```\n.env file / system environment\n        │\n        ▼\n  os.environ.get(...)\n        │\n        ▼\n  Settings class (app/settings.py)\n    ├── Raw attributes (ALLOWED_HOST, SECRET_KEY, DEBUG, PORT)\n    ├── Composed attributes (DB_URL, TEST_DB_URL)\n    ├── Hardcoded attributes (token expiry, JWT algorithm, page size)\n    └── Defaults (REDIS_HOST=\"localhost\", REDIS_PORT=\"6379\")\n        │\n        ▼\n  Consumed by:\n    ├── main.py (server config)\n    ├── app/db.py (database connections)\n    └── auth/services.py (JWT token creation, password hashing)\n```\n\nThe design is simple and explicit: a single `Settings` object is the single source of truth, instantiated once at import time, and shared across the entire application.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1793, "prompt_tokens": 7131, "total_tokens": 8924, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 486, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 6656, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0005871768, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 8.51368e-05, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00050204}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780871986-II0oQTHt6jZ16uHntG9N", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea43d-fc92-7ae2-b4b1-1257edc28746-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 7131, "output_tokens": 1793, "total_tokens": 8924, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 6656}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 486}}}}]}}}
